[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm working on a different project that is a plugin API for a p2p node, and while I was playing the rust module API I think, \"Ehi wait a minute, I already see this pattern\"</p>\n<p>and I was thinking if maybe was already discussed late in the time and I missed it to write the module as a procedural macros?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[module_init]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_name</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello world</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I did not experment on it, but I could</p>",
        "id": 303118312,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665313092
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the procedural macros will expand in the trait and so on, I think that in order to do that I may pass the struct name in the procedural macro</p>",
        "id": 303118378,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665313145
    },
