    {
        "content": "<p>What's the advantage?</p>",
        "id": 303137334,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1665324334
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/init.20and.20drop.20module.20with.20a.20procedural.20macro/near/303137334\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What's the advantage?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>maybe is more C friendly?</p>\n<p>The rust version is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_name</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello world</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 303137952,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665324741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but the C version is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">int</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">hello_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">void</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">printk</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">KERN_INFO</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello World</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">EXIT_WITH_SUCCESS</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"n\">module_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hello_init</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>That it is very similar to </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[module_init]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_name</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello world</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">HelloModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But again, my is not te proposal, is just a question if it was already take in consideration! To see the advantage imho we should implement it and see how it goes</p>",
        "id": 303138118,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665324877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could laos have a init method that accept incremental parameter, in this case the init can be just with 0 argument</p>",
        "id": 303138174,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665324922
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, I don't think we ever considered in. In general we try to keep the number of proc-macros to an absolute minimum. <code>module_init</code> also needs to be part of the same abstraction as <code>module_exit</code>, in order to be type-safe.</p>",
        "id": 303138197,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1665324950
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/init.20and.20drop.20module.20with.20a.20procedural.20macro/near/303138197\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>No, I don't think we ever considered in. In general we try to keep the number of proc-macros to an absolute minimum. <code>module_init</code> also needs to be part of the same abstraction as <code>module_exit</code>, in order to be type-safe.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, procedural macros are not very good to base all the project, but I think as in this case where there is an old API that can be match with these  language functionality can be good to have.</p>\n<p>But again, I'm still studing the rust codebase, and maybe there are case where the API will completly messup :)</p>\n<p>I will try to give a shot and in the free time, maybe there is somethings good to explore</p>",
        "id": 303138858,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1665325370
    }
]